cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM. 

This paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks to detect clinical dermoscopic features from skin lesion images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training the network to minimize a smoothed negative F1 score, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the second most likely category. The use of neural networks for image classification and segmentation also suggests the categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as possible categories. Finally, the use of dermoscopy images suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia).
